original: Björck, Carl Gustaf Ingemar, kyrkoherde, Gotlands Hässelby, f. 31/10/ 14 i Mörbylånga, Kalmar 1., av tillf, kyrkoh. Ernst B. o. Anna Holmdahl. G. 43 m. Ulla Blix. Barn: Christina f. 44, Joban 46. — Stud:ex. i Borås 33, ’teol. fii’L ex. 35, teol. kand. 39, prakt, teok prov 39, allt i Upps., prästv. i Gbg f. Visby stift 40. Kyrkoadj. i Rute, Fårö’sund 40, marinpastoT v. Gotl. kusitant :kår 40, domkyrkoadj. i Visby 43, mil:pastor v. Gotl. art :kår 43, las :-pred. v. Gotl. k las. 43, kyrkoh. i Dalhems past. ised. 44.
translated: Björck, Carl Gustaf Ingemar, pastor, Gotlands Hässelby, born on October 31st, 1914 in Mörbylånga, Kalmar County. He is the son of Ernst B. and Anna Holmdahl who was a priest. He got married to Ulla Blix in 1943 and they have two children, Christina born in 1944 and Joban born in 1946. Carl Gustaf completed his secondary education in Borås in 1933, his theology exams in 1935, and earned a degree in theology in 1939, all in Uppsala. He was ordained as a priest in Gothenburg for the Visby diocese in 1940. He served as a church assistant in Rute and Fårö’sund in 1940, marine pastor for the Gotland Coastal Artillery in 1940, cathedral assistant in Visby in 1943, military pastor for the Gotland Coastal Artillery in 1943, chaplain for the Gotland Garrison in 1943, and finally became a pastor in Dalhem in 1944.
